A new set of 180 cards for the [Pok√©mon Trading Card Game](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Trading_Card_Game) (TCG) will be released on [September 26th](https://www.pokemon.com/us/pokemon-tcg/mega-evolution) 2025. What started as a collecting card game for children, has evolved into a passion for children and adults alike. In recent years, mainly during the COVID-19 pandemic, the hobby has garnered an even greater audience, causing increased demand for the printed cardboard.&#x20;

Sets of cards are printed in limited quantity for a limited time. Some particularly rare or interesting cards (e.g. cards featuring well known characters) have been [sold for more than 150,000\$](https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/53510751), with more typical values ranging [between](https://www.tcgplayer.com/product/610516/pokemon-sv-prismatic-evolutions-umbreon-ex-161-131?page=1\&Language=English) 100-1000\$. Some have turned the game into a business, buying a large quantity of booster packs (containing random cards) from retail stores and reselling them for higher prices, or investing in specific cards, hoping their value will increase.

Other sets released earlier this year, include *Destined Rivals* and *Black Blaze,* whose most expensive cards have values of 349\$ and 433\$ respectively, according to [tcgplayer.com](https://www.tcgplayer.com/search/pokemon/product?view=grid\&productLineName=pokemon\&setName=sv-black-bolt|sv10-destined-rivals\&page=1) at the time of writing this question.

[Ebola](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebola) is a viral hemorrhagic fever with a case fatality rate of around 50%. Since its discovery in 1976, periodic outbreaks have occurred mainly across West and Central Africa.&#x20;

According to the [WHO](https://www.afro.who.int/countries/democratic-republic-of-congo/news/democratic-republic-congo-declares-ebola-virus-disease-outbreak-kasai-province), the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) declared a new Ebola outbreak in Kasa√Ø Province on September 4, 2025. As of September 7, there have been 32 cases and 15 deaths associated with the outbreak.&#x20;

Due to a vaccine approved in 2019, most recent Ebola outbreaks have been contained after a few cases. Prior to the current outbreak, the last outbreak exceeding 25 cases took place in Uganda in 2022. The last large outbreak in the DRC was the Kivu Ebola epidemic which sickened and killed thousands of people from 2018 to 2020. This question aims to estimate the eventual scale of the current outbreak.

In August 2025, plant-based protein manufacturer Beyond Meat [denied](https://plantbasednews.org/news/economics/beyond-meat-denies-filing-for-bankruptcy/) filing bankruptcy in response to what it called "unequivocally false" rumors. Its quarterly and annual reports can be read [here](https://www.sec.gov/edgar/browse/?CIK=1655210\&owner=exclude), including its most recent [quarterly report](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1655210/000165521025000159/bynd-20250628.htm), which showed it down to \$103 million in cash, declining revenues, and -\$65.4 million in free cash flow in the 6 months through June 28, 2025.&#x20;

See also from The Food Institute: [Beyond Meat on the Verge of Financial Ruin](https://foodinstitute.com/focus/beyond-meat-on-the-verge-of-financial-ruin/)

Also from Metaculus: [Will Beyond Meat file for bankruptcy protection before 2026?](https://www.metaculus.com/questions/12112/beyond-meat-bankruptcy-before-2026/)

[The Fide Grand Swiss](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE_Grand_Swiss_Tournament) is a large, Swiss-style chess tournament organised by FIDE every year, and forms part of the qualifying cycle for the Candidates Tournament - the top 2 players in the Grand Swiss qualify for the candidates.

[The Tournament this year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE_Grand_Swiss_Tournament_2025) will take place in Samarkand, Uzbekistan, and will consist of 11 rounds of classical chess from the 3rd to the 16th of September 2025. There are 116 players qualified for the tournament - the top 101 rated players who accept their invitation, plus 4 continental qualifiers, 4 nominees from the host country, and 6 nominees by the president of FIDE.&#x20;

Full tournament regulation [are here](https://handbook.fide.com/files/handbook/Regulations_for_the_FIDE_Grand_Swiss_2025.pdf).&#x20;

Three results are possible in the game of chess: black win, white win, or a draw. In typical chess terminology, black or white wins are considered decisive results, whilst draws are not decisive results. Chess is thought to be a "drawish" game, with many observers finding the lack of decisive results, particularly at the highest level of chess competition, frustrating.&#x20;

The past three FIDE Grand Swiss tournaments had the following percentages/numbers of decisive games:&#x20;

* [2023](https://www.fide.com/grand-swiss-a-look-beyond-the-individual-games-and-results/): 441 draws from 840 games (52.5% draw rate)
* [2021](https://www.reddit.com/r/chess/comments/qpexh5/grand_swiss_data_and_closing_statistics/): 53% draw rate
* [2019](https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chess.pl?result=1/2-1/2\&tid=105290): 320 draws from 594 games (53.9% draw rate)&#x20;

Tensions have been rising between the United States and Venezuela, as the US has been deploying military assets around Venezuela. According to the [New York Times](https://www.nytimes.com/2025/09/05/us/politics/trump-maduro-military-venezuela.html):&#x20;

> The military so far has deployed eight warships, several Navy P-8 surveillance planes and one attack submarine to the region. The Pentagon has offered few details on the force‚Äôs objectives and locations.

> The Iwo Jima Amphibious Ready Group ‚Äî including the U.S.S. San Antonio, the U.S.S. Iwo Jima and the U.S.S. Fort Lauderdale, carrying 4,500 sailors ‚Äîwas steaming near Puerto Rico on Friday, Defense Department officials said. So was the 22nd Marine Expeditionary Unit, with 2,200 Marines. The Iwo Jima is equipped with AV-8B Harrier attack aircraft.

> Two Navy guided-missile destroyers ‚Äî the U.S.S. Jason Dunham and the U.S.S. Gravely ‚Äî are operating in the southern Caribbean. Both warships had recently joined the campaign against the Houthi militia in the Red Sea. A third destroyer, the U.S.S. Sampson, now in the eastern Pacific, may soon join, one Navy official said.

There have been [calls](https://thehill.com/opinion/international/5471918-the-us-should-overthrow-maduro-in-venezuela/) within the US to overthrow Maduro, and the White House has [described](https://www.foxnews.com/video/6377091663112) Maduro as a "narco-terror" leader. However, US President Donald J. Trump on September 5, 2025 [denied](https://www.cnn.com/2025/09/05/politics/trump-weighs-strikes-targeting-cartels-inside-venezuela) the US is seeking regime change in Venezuela.&#x20;

