An explicitly temporary suspension of a campaign, such as John McCain's 2008 "[suspension](https://www.npr.org/2008/09/25/95038824/charting-mccains-suspended-campaign)" of his campaign for US president, will not count unless it becomes indefinite.

A dropped-out candidate need not be removed from NYC's electoral ballot; according to media reports ([CNN](https://www.cnn.com/2025/06/26/politics/cuomo-mamdani-mayor-november-ballot)) the withdrawal deadline to be removed from the ballot has already expired.&#x20;

